<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1906,2041]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,465]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1978,2004]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Discussion:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[393,491,1979,2005]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">holotype</typeStatus>
has intact forelegs but is missing all other tarsi and right hindleg distal to the femur (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,2015,2041]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1620,1644]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,669,1597]" captionTargetId="figure-264@12.[151,1435,669,1597]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 24–25. Cryphocricos rufus (24) holotype, dorsal, (25) allotype, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693102/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). The female 
<typeStatus box="[400,490,2015,2041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">allotype</typeStatus>
has intact forelegs and left hindleg (
<figureCitation box="[904,989,2014,2041]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1620,1644]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,669,1597]" captionTargetId="figure-264@12.[151,1435,669,1597]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 24–25. Cryphocricos rufus (24) holotype, dorsal, (25) allotype, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693102/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), but the middle legs are complete only through the tibiae and the right hindleg through the femur (
<figureCitation box="[801,885,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,959,983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,935]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1435,181,935]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Holotypes of (21) Cryphocricos obscuratus, dorsal, (22) Cryphocricos peruvianus, dorsal and (23) Cryphocricos peruvianus, ventral. Figure 23 courtesy of H.D.D. Rodrigues." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693096/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Glue to hold the 
<typeStatus box="[1086,1176,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">allotype</typeStatus>
to the pin has obscured the view of the pterothoracic ventral midline, leg bases, and the left side of the metasternum through abdominal sternum IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="85" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,258,284]" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Roback" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[616,773,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruvianus">
<emphasis box="[616,773,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">C. peruvianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the reddish-brown color, smaller size, laterally rounded hemelytra, and deep concavity in the anterior margin of the pronotum (
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[961,1134,295,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" pagination="426 - 433" refId="ref12276" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1940) I) Descripcion de tres especies nuevas del genero Cryphocricus Signoret. II). Una nueva especie del genero Heleocoris Stal (Hemiptera-Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 10, 426 - 433." type="journal article" year="1940">De Carlo 1940</bibRefCitation>
). In the key to brachypterous specimens, 
<bibRefCitation author="Usinger, R. L." box="[328,498,331,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" pagination="329 - 343" refId="ref14212" refString="Usinger, R. L. (1947) Classification of the Cryphocricinae (Hemiptera: Naucoridae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 40, 329 - 343. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 40.2.329" type="journal article" year="1947">Usinger (1947)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1940" box="[661,752,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis box="[661,752,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">C. rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1940" box="[819,961,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daguerrei">
<emphasis box="[819,961,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">C. daguerrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the evenly curved lateral margin of the abdomen, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[329,450,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis box="[329,450,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Roback" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[505,661,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruvianus">
<emphasis box="[505,661,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">C. peruvianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the rounded apical and lateral margins of the hemelytra, and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Usinger" authorityYear="1947" box="[151,278,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breddini">
<emphasis box="[151,278,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">C. breddini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the body more than half as wide as long. The posterior margin of the subgenital plate of the 
<typeStatus box="[1346,1436,403,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">allotype</typeStatus>
is broadly concave with rounded posterolateral corners (
<figureCitation box="[781,865,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1620,1644]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,669,1597]" captionTargetId="figure-264@12.[151,1435,669,1597]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 24–25. Cryphocricos rufus (24) holotype, dorsal, (25) allotype, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693102/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="85">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
